If $r_u = r_v$:
A cycle is formed. The path $P_{u,v}$ in the existing graph has parity $p_{u,v}$.
$P_{u,v}$ goes from $u \to r_u$ and $r_u \to v$.
$p_{u,v} \equiv p_u \oplus p_v \pmod 2$. (Since $p_u$ is $u \to r_u$ and $p_v$ is $v \to r_v$, and $r_u=r_v$, the path $u \to v$ is $u \to r_u \to v$. The parity is $p_u \oplus p_v$).

The new edge $(u, v, w)$ completes the cycle. The cycle weight is $w + p_{u,v}$.
We must check if $w + p_{u,v} \equiv 0 \pmod 2$.
$w \equiv p_{u,v} \pmod 2$.
$w \equiv p_u \oplus p_v \pmod 2$.

If this condition holds, the edge is added. If it does not hold, the edge is rejected.

